body:
@binarycrusader, your commits are fine (which happened right after we last ran the script for Go 1.5's release). Your commits (your email) are associated with Oracle's CLA. If I re-ran the script today, Oracle would be included in the list based on your commits. The script works.

But @4ad, how would my A+C update script ever know that Oracle owned your copyright for commits coming from your personal email address?

I'm not sure why @rsc gave you that advice, or what the context was. I will work with @adg and @ianlancetaylor and others to update the docs to make this more clear.
